Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Japan's economy, Louise Woodward and homosexuality
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00yjmjj
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 19 Jun 1998
US intervention in Japan's economy, Louise Woodward returns to the UK after her life sentence is reduced and Republican Trent Lott calls homosexuality a sin on national TV.